“ After having made ourselves familiar with the spirit of any given period, from a study of the dif- ferent writers of the period itself, we should turn to a history of it written by a modern writer, and observe how its peculiarities accord with those of a different age, and what judgment is passed by posterity upon its favourite views and practices.”
